  {
    "id": 3,
    "key": "incinedile",
    "name": "Incinedile",
    "description": "Tutorial-floor boss ('Incineradile' in the GDD/compendium). Apparent giant flamethrower reptile \u2014 actually a mycelium puppet: a network inside controls the body, reattaches limbs, and vents pressure by exploding. Pre-breach damage is cosmetic only; the party must discover the breach. Fully play-tested at the live table. Boss music: God Shattering Star. Cinematic intro: gates close, freeze, 'Party vs Boss' announcement, caged band above the arena.",
    "category": "Boss",
    "size": "Huge",
    "body_parts": [
      {
        "key": "network",
        "name": "Network",
        "hp": 50,
        "lethal": true,
        "hidden_until_breach": true,
        "bleed_immune": true,
        "bleed_immune_note": "The mycelium core is a separate organism \u2014 it doesn't bleed. Bleeding never applies to it and systemic bleed-out never drains it; the puppet's flesh can be bled, the network cannot. Finish it with crushing/HP damage after the breach (F2 rework, owner ruling 2026-07-19).",
        "condition_immunities": [
          "crushed",
          "chilled",
          "exhausted",
          "infected",
          "suffocation",
          "dissolution",
          "poison"
        ],
        "fire_harms": true,
        "network_profile_note": "Owner ruling 2026-07-20: the network is a body part with its OWN resistances \u2014 immune to most conditions (they never apply, so nothing wears it down as a condition), NO resistance to force (full HP damage grinds its 50 HP), and fire HARMS it (fire_harms exempts it from the boss's fire-heal \u2014 mycelium burns). Neural poison (poison_type 'neural') bypasses the poison immunity \u2014 mycelium is a neural network."
      },
